      "text": [
        " عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ : \"أَيُّمَا رَجُلٍ اِشْتَرَى مِنْ رَجُلٍ بَيْعاً فَهُمَا بِالْخِيَارِ حَتَّى يَفْتَرِقَا فَإِذَا اِفْتَرَقَا فَقَدْ وَجَبَ اَلْبَيْعُ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.3762 - Imam (as) said: \"Whenever a man buys something from another man, they both have the option (to cancel the deal) until they part ways. Once they part, the sale becomes binding.\""
        ]
      }
    },
